                    <msContents>
                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>This is a fragmentary record engraved in Pallava-Grantha characters of the 7th century A.D. A major portion of the inscription is erased, but from the preserved portion, the names of musical notes such as <hi rend="italic">gāndhāram, pañchamam, dhaivatam, nishādam</hi> etc., can be read. A certain order is noticeable in the arrangement of the notes in seven sections with subsections. Unfortunately the subsections have been so erased as to make it impossible to follow the method adopted here. As the palaeography of the inscription resembles that of the Kuḍimiyāmalai epigraph, this record also may be attributed to the time of Mahēndravarman l.</p>						
                            
                        </summary>
                    </msContents>
